A multitude of party chiefs and supporters thronged the Adamawa APC secretariat as a former governor of the state, Mohammed Umaru Jibrilla Bindow, declared his intention to join the guber race. Sen. Jibrilla Bindow, a former Governor of Adamawa who joined the governorship race in the state on the platform of All Progressives Congress (APC) attracted a huge crowd of well-wishers at the venue to witness his declaration. Bindow said he would revamp the economy, and transmit the dividends of democracy to all citizens of Adamawa State. He also said that he finally resolved to re-contest in order to complete his second term in office. He added that all APC governorship aspirants were qualified; urging them to give him a chance to continue from where he stopped for further development and to rescue the people from extreme poverty. Bindow appealed to the electorates to give him the opportunity to serve the state for a second term. “I did a lot in the state when I was Governor and I had many plans for the state but we lost the 2019 elections due to infighting but hopefully if reelected in 2023” he would shock the people with stupendous wealth creation and development. In his remarks, Alhaji Ibrahim Bilal, the state APC Chairman called for unity of the party. POLL He advised all aspirants to work harmoniously towards achieving a common goal of winning the state in 2023. Bindow revealed that understanding and unity among party members were essential for the progress of the party ahead of the 2023 general elections. Bindow was elected governor of Adamawa State in 2015 before losing his second term bid in 2019.